$interpreted: Jerome: Mr. Nigel, thank you for taking care of us these past few days.
Nigel: It was nothing. Don't mention it.
Nigel: The demihumans loved the fair and we even resolved the issue with the bandits.
Nigel: ...I must thank you for that.
Lio: Excellent. When Angel hears this she'll be delighted!
Nigel: Ha, I hope so.
Nigel: Speaking of which...that general of yours?
Jerome: Hmm, General...? General──
Fredrica: Don't worry, handsome. I'm here, aren't I?
Leah: Hey Fredrica, why are you still wearing that?
Fredrica: Bunny-boo, have you forgotten?
Fredrica: I've finished my task flawlessly. Now I've got seven full days of vacation~
Fredrica: If I, Fredrica Lucien, have days off, not even one second of one minute shall be wasted!
Lio: General Lucien is also so...so cool...when I get older...can I become as cool as her?
Leah: No! Absolutely not──!
Jerome: General, you are going to lead this boy astray...
Nigel: Hey, you all are way too loud...
Yamitsuki: ...Ha.
Nigel: What are you laughing at?
Yamitsuki: Just reminiscing.
Nigel: ...What's the matter now?
Izumi: Heehee, I just found out that your conversation is flowing quite naturally~
Izumi: Not all awkward like before...
Yamitsuki: ...That's not true.
Nigel: Hey, this is how we've always talked.
Izumi: Ahaha, oh really?
Izumi: Actually~ you two disappeared for a little while. I followed you from behind...
Nigel: W-W-W-What did you just say──
Yamitsuki: Liar...I didn't sense you.
Izumi: Aigh-ya, Yamitsuki, I may not be as amazing as you, but I'm an expert at sneaking around!
Izumi: It's easy to hide and not be found~
Yamitsuki: ...I don't believe you.
Izumi: Ah, I think I saw Yamitsuki and Nigel heading into the castle...
Izumi: ...and then──
Yamitsuki: ...Don't think about running!
Izumi: Wah, Yamitsuki's mad~Quick, run!
Jerome: Wah! What are you doing, Miss Yamitsuki...
Nigel: Be careful! Get out of the way!
Fredrica: Hey, you ruined my outfit~
Leah: Geez, each one of 'em is more childish than the last. I can't believe my cute little brother is spending his days with these people.
Leah: How am I supposed to leave here feeling assured?
Lio: ...Sis, you...
Lio: Next time you're off, will you come see me?
Lio: ...*sigh*...didn't think you'd laugh at me...
Leah: I'm laughing at you on purpose, stupid brother.
Leah: Hey, here ya go!
Lio: Flutterfly...? It-It looks different...
Leah: I heard you talk about its design and structure, so I made one myself.
Leah: Even though it doesn't fly very far...call it Flutterfly 2.0, whatta you think?
Lio: It flies! My sister's amazing!
Leah: Heehee, you like that prank?
Lio: Hey! I like my sister the most!
Leah: ...Sorry, Lio.
Leah: I can't spend a lot of time with you. I can only come see you every so often...
Lio: It's okay, sis...I'm doing great. I'm so happy we got to play together and go to the fair...
Lio: Plus, when we grow up, we can see each other every day!
Leah: Wah, we gotta wait that long?
Lio: I'll do my best!
Lio: Work hard to become as cool as Jerome, meet more new friends, and protect my sister...
Lio: Wah, so many dreams~
Leah: ...Haha, stupid brother.
Leah: This vacation was so...freaking awesome!
Carterwell Ambassador: ...As I mentioned, thank you General, for helping with the promotion.
Carterwell Ambassador: This swimwear has become a major trend in the Kingdom of the Sun.
Fredrica: When I'm involved, that's inevitable.
Fredrica: Not to mention your craftsmanship is excellent. Being able to perfectly implement my designs, really worth commending~
Sharice: ...Didn't think things would turn out like this...
Fredrica: What'd you say, wimp?
Sharice: N-Nothing...
Fredrica: Heehee, good~
Fredrica: Yes, as for the new business plan you mentioned in your letter...
Carterwell Ambassador: Yes. According to market research, it's not only humans who are interested in these outfits.
Fredrica: Really?
Carterwell Ambassador: Surprised? We've already received many letters. The East Alliance is our next target.
Sharice: Isn't that...the Beasts' territory?
Carterwell Ambassador: Industry is not confined by borders, Miss Sharice.
Carterwell Ambassador: That is why, General Lucien, I implore you to come up with some apparel for the Beasts.
Carterwell Ambassador: Like for the Tiger Tribe. Perhaps they'll like it!
Fredrica: Sounds pretty good. Unfortunately, I don't have any Tiger friends to be my model~
Sharice: Tiger...tiger...
Sharice: ...Ah!
Sharice: ......W-What?
Fredrica: Hey wimp, do you have someone in mind? Excellent, introduce them to me, please~
Sharice: Crap, crap, crap...
Fredrica: Accept your fate, wimp...!
Fredrica: Give me their name!
Sharice: ...I don't wanna!!!!!!
